I've only been here once, but my only complaint was that my belly wasn't big enough for all of the food that I ordered. I had a sandwich, wine and a bruschetta board. Everything was good, but I'd say the bruschetta board is really the item to visit for. Different flavors and choices. Combinations that you aren't sure should work are delicious. So when I crave a girls night with the works, I intend to come here for wine and bruschetta boards!

